					<msContents>
						<summary>
							<p>Copy of a palm-leaf order. Grant of money (<foreign>paṇam</foreign>) by the <foreign>tēvaraṭiyār</foreign> Nāṟpatteṇṇāyira-Naṅkai to the temple for the benefit of mendicants (<foreign>kōvaṇavar</foreign>), devotees of Vīrabhadra (<foreign>vīrapattirar</foreign>) and temple trustees (<foreign>tāṉattar</foreign>). In return, she was appointed to perform several services, including flashing the sacred fly-whisk (<foreign>tiruveṇcāmarai</foreign>), the sacred mirror (<foreign>tirukkaṇṇāṭi</foreign>), the recitation of holy hymns (<foreign>tiruppāṭṭu</foreign>) while gesturing with her hands (<foreign>kaikāṭṭa</foreign>), as well as certain land rights (<foreign>urimai kuṭi</foreign>).</p>						
				</summary>
			</msContents>
			<physDesc>
				<handDesc>
					<p>ARIE dates the inscription to the 14th century on palaeographical grounds.</p>
				</handDesc>
			</physDesc>
		</msDesc>
